			<div class="text-block">
				<h3>Rural Transformation</h3>
				<p>This cell started its activities in the 3rd week of this semester and has done appreciable amount of work. Various programs under which the events were conducted are: 
				<h3>EDUSLUM:</h3>
				RT education is an initiative towards providing quality education to unprivileged bright students of our villages. We provide one to one assistance to children in their weak areas in studies. Special workshops are organised for those preparing for competitive examinations. Since one year we are carrying out this activity, till date around 50 students have been benefited by the program. We aim at providing real education and make them better citizen.  
				<h3>SURVEYS:</h3>
				It is an initiative taken to educate the slum children at Teliwala Primary School(behind Roorkee Railway Station) with 5 classes weekly being organized by the volunteers from NSS. 
				<h3>RT EDUCATION (Disha):</h3>
				Apart from regular teaching activities like Eduslum and Disha, a survey was conducted on the kids (under 14) working in IIT Roorkee canteens.
Another survey was conducted under ‘Stimulating Education & Enhancing Development’ (SEED) project of NSS IIT Roorkee with the mission of ‘Every Child Attends School and Learns Well’, to find the scenario of education status of children under the age of 16 working in the market places of Kaliyar and Manglore. As a part of the survey 150 children were interviewed by around 55 students of the cell. 
The cell also helped Pratham, an NGO in preparing the ASER (Annual Status of Education Report) survey report by conducting surveys in 30 villages of Haridwar district on Nov 13. The survey was conducted nationwide by NGO Pratham with the help of volunteers from across the country to submit a report on the status of school education in India to the policy makers of our country (Planning Commission).The report was released by Dr. Ansari(Vice President of India) on 15th January , 2011


